"title": "8402: claims",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8402",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The assertion of rights and recognition due. God as Creator and Redeemer makes claims on his world and on his people. The claims of Jesus Christ about himself as God and Messiah call for a response. In human relationships, too, claims are made by individuals about themselves and, as a result, on others.</p>\n<h2>The basis for God's claims</h2>\n<h3>God's ownership of the world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps24:1-Ps24:2\">PSA 24:1–24:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:14\">DEU 10:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:11\">JOB 41:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps47:9\">PSA 47:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:11\">PSA 89:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:4\">EZK 18:4</a></p>\n<h3>God owns his people as Creator</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:6\">DEU 32:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:6-Isa43:7\">ISA 43:6–43:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:15\">ISA 43:15</a></p>\n<h3>God owns his people as Redeemer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:19-1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:19–6:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:2-Exod20:3\">EXO 20:2–20:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:6-Deut5:7\">DEU 5:6–5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:55\">LEV 25:55</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:1\">ISA 43:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:8\">ROM 14:8</a></p>\n<h2>The priority of God's claims</h2>\n<h3>God's claim to first place</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:33\">MAT 6:33</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:31\">LUK 12:31</a></p>\n<h3>God's claim on the firstborn</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:2\">EXO 13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:19\">EXO 34:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:26\">LEV 27:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:13\">NUM 3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:36\">NEH 10:36</a></p>\n<h3>God's claim to the firstfruits</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut26:1-Deut26:2\">DEU 26:1–26:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:35\">NEH 10:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:9\">PRO 3:9</a></p>\n<h3>God's claim to the tithe</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:30\">LEV 27:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:8-Mal3:10\">MAL 3:8–3:10</a></p>\n<h2>Acknowledging God's claims on human life</h2>\n<h3>Wholehearted devotion to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:4-Deut6:5\">DEU 6:4–6:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:37\">MAT 22:37</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:30\">MRK 12:30</a></p>\n<h3>Obedience to God's law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:4-Lev18:5\">LEV 18:4–18:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:37\">LEV 19:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:31\">LEV 22:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:19\">EZK 20:19</a></p>\n<h3>The call to holiness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:45\">LEV 11:45</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:2\">LEV 19:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:7\">LEV 20:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:26\">LEV 20:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:15-1Pet1:16\">1PE 1:15–1:16</a></p>\n<h3>Honouring God's name</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:12\">LEV 19:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:32-Lev22:33\">LEV 22:32–22:33</a></p>\n<h3>Observing the Sabbath</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:3\">LEV 19:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:30\">LEV 19:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:2\">LEV 26:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:20\">EZK 20:20</a></p>\n<h3>Not worshipping idols</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:4\">LEV 19:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:1\">LEV 26:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:10\">JDG 6:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:8\">ISA 42:8</a></p>\n<h2>The claims of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's claim to fulfil the OT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:17\">MAT 5:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:17-Luke4:21\">LUK 4:17–4:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:27\">LUK 24:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:39\">JHN 5:39</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus' claim to be the Messiah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:2\">LUK 23:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:10\">MAT 23:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:41\">MRK 9:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:67\">LUK 22:67</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:25-John4:26\">JHN 4:25–4:26</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's claim to be king of the Jews</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:11\">MAT 27:11</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:2\">MRK 15:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:3\">LUK 23:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:12\">JHN 19:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:21\">JHN 19:21</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's claim to divinity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:33\">JHN 10:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:7\">JHN 19:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:63-Matt26:64\">MAT 26:63–26:64</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:61-Mark14:62\">MRK 14:61–14:62</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:70\">LUK 22:70</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:43\">MAT 27:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:7\">MRK 2:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:21\">LUK 5:21</a> <em>Forgiveness of sin was recognised as the prerogative of God alone. Jesus Christ's claim to forgive sin is thus a claim to be God</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:30\">JHN 10:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:9\">JHN 14:9</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's claim to universal lordship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:18\">MAT 28:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31-Matt25:32\">MAT 25:31–25:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:69\">LUK 22:69</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:2\">JHN 17:2</a></p>\n<h3>The ``I am'' claims of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:58\">JHN 8:58</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:35\">JHN 6:35</a> <em>the bread of life</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:12\">JHN 8:12</a> <em>the light of the world</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:7\">JHN 10:7</a> <em>the gate for the sheep</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:11\">JHN 10:11</a> <em>the good shepherd</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:25\">JHN 11:25</a> <em>the resurrection and the life</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:6\">JHN 14:6</a> <em>the way and the truth and the life</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:1\">JHN 15:1</a> <em>the true vine</em></p>\n<h3>The need to acknowledge Jesus Christ's claims</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:24-John8:30\">JHN 8:24–8:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:11\">JHN 14:11</a></p>\n<h2>Human claims</h2>\n<h3>Those making claims about themselves</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:9\">PSA 73:9</a> <em>the proud boasting of the wicked</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:34\">JER 23:34</a> <em>false prophets claim to speak God's word</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:5\">MAT 24:5</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:6\">MRK 13:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:8\">LUK 21:8</a> <em>false Christs</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:36\">ACT 5:36</a> <em>Theudas</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:9\">ACT 8:9</a> <em>Simon the sorcerer claimed to be someone great</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:22\">ROM 1:22</a> <em>idolaters claim to be wise</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:16\">JUD 1:16</a> <em>false teachers in the church</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:2\">REV 2:2</a> <em>false apostles</em></p>\n<h3>Claims must be verified by actions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:14\">JAS 2:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:6\">PRO 20:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:16\">TIT 1:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:6\">1JN 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:6\">1JN 2:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:9\">1JN 2:9</a></p>\n<h3>Making claims on others</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:3\">2SA 15:3</a> <em>grievances brought for judgment</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:43\">2SA 19:43</a> <em>Israel's claim on David as their king</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh2:20\">NEH 2:20</a> <em>Nehemiah's enemies have no claim on Jerusalem.</em></p>\n<h3>Claims made about others</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:20\">PSA 35:20</a> <em>false accusations made against the righteous</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:11\">MAT 5:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:22\">LUK 6:22</a> <em>Believers will be slandered by their enemies</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:18-Luke11:20\">LUK 11:18–11:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:26-Matt12:28\">MAT 12:26–12:28</a> <em>The Jews claim that Jesus Christ's powers are demonic</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:8\">ROM 3:8</a> <em>slanderous claims made against Paul</em></p>",
